<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="184" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,756,1587,1804]" pageId="19" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,285,1587,1610]" pageId="19" pageNumber="184">Comments:</emphasis>
We have examined the types of this species and found that all the specimens (
<typeStatus box="[613,708,1619,1642]" pageId="19" pageNumber="184">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[151,256,1652,1675]" pageId="19" pageNumber="184">paratypes</typeStatus>
) belong without doubt to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reitter, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larvata">
<emphasis box="[583,756,1651,1675]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="184">Achilia larvata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter E." box="[158,306,1684,1707]" pageId="19" pageNumber="184" pagination="321 - 332" refId="ref11686" refString="Reitter E. 1885. Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Pselaphiden-Fauna von Valdivia, Zweiter Theil. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 29: 321 - 332, pl. II." type="journal article" year="1885">Reitter, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, one of the species we recently revised (
<bibRefCitation author="Sabella G. &amp; Kurbatov S. A. &amp; Cuccodoro G." box="[158,380,1716,1740]" pageId="19" pageNumber="184" pagination="119 - 140" refId="ref11734" refString="Sabella G., Kurbatov S. A., Cuccodoro G. 2017. A revision of the Chilean Brachyglutini - Part 2. Revision of Achilia Reitter, 1890: A. crassicornis, A. tumidifrons, A. bifossifrons and A. lobifera species group (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Pselaphinae). Revue suisse de Zoologie 124 (1): 119 - 140." type="journal article" year="2017">
Sabella 
<emphasis box="[249,299,1716,1740]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="184">et al</emphasis>
., 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore we here place 
<taxonomicName authority="Franz, 1996" authorityName="Franz" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="validicorniformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="184">Achilia validicorniformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Franz H." box="[349,482,1748,1771]" pageId="19" pageNumber="184" pagination="83 - 146" refId="ref11459" refString="Franz H. 1996. Neue Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pselaphidenfauna von Chile und Argentinien (Coleoptera: Pselaphidae). Koleopterologische Rundschau 66: 83 - 146." type="journal article" year="1996">Franz, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reitter, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[151,421,1780,1804]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larvata">
<emphasis box="[151,258,1780,1804]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="184">A. larvata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter E." box="[272,413,1781,1804]" pageId="19" pageNumber="184" pagination="321 - 332" refId="ref11686" refString="Reitter E. 1885. Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Pselaphiden-Fauna von Valdivia, Zweiter Theil. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 29: 321 - 332, pl. II." type="journal article" year="1885">Reitter, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[436,535,1781,1804]" pageId="19" pageNumber="184">syn. nov.</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
